    • Method Detail

      • getMaxParseChars

        long getMaxParseChars()
        Get the maximum number of parsed characters. This provides a limit on the maximum number of characters that will be parsed before throwing an exception. The default value is DEFAULT_MAX_PARSE_CHARS.

      • getMaxParseChars

        static long getMaxParseChars(JsonUrlLimits limits)
        Get the maximum number of parsed characters, providing the default if necessary.
        Parameters:
        limits - a valid JsonUrlLimits or null.
        See Also:
        getMaxParseChars()

      • getMaxParseDepth

        int getMaxParseDepth()
        Get the maximum parse depth. This provides a limit on the depth of a JSON→URL object/array before an exception of thrown. The default value is DEFAULT_MAX_PARSE_DEPTH.

      • getMaxParseDepth

        static int getMaxParseDepth(JsonUrlLimits limits)
        Get the maximum number of parsed depth, providing the default if necessary.
        Parameters:
        limits - a valid JsonUrlLimits or null.
        See Also:
        getMaxParseDepth()

      • getMaxParseValues

        int getMaxParseValues()
        Set the maximum number of parsed values. This provides a limit on the number of values that will be parsed/instantiated before an exception is thrown. The default value is DEFAULT_MAX_PARSE_VALUES.

      • getMaxParseValues

        static int getMaxParseValues(JsonUrlLimits limits)
        Get the maximum number of parsed values, providing the default if necessary.
        Parameters:
        limits - a valid JsonUrlLimits or null.
        See Also:
        getMaxParseValues()
